canonical:
  title: 幽谷驛館
  author: 洪彦忠
  language: lzh
  text: 一枕淸風孤舘裏三杯薄酒老槐邊此行不料生還日萬事悠悠只付天
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 幽谷驛館
  author: 洪彦忠
  language: lzh
  text: 一枕淸風孤舘裏。三杯薄酒老槐邊。此行不料生還日。萬事悠悠只付天。
korean:
  title: 유곡 역관
  author: 홍언충
  language: kor
  text: |-
    한 베개 맑은 바람 외로운 객관 속에
    늙은 괴목 가에 박주 석잔 기울였네
    이 걸음에 살아 옴을 내 어이 생각하랴
    유유한 만 가지 일일랑은 하늘에다 붙이련다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1460_010_0440&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: At the Yougu Waystation
  author: Hong Eon-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A pillow of clear wind in this lonely inn—
    Beside the ancient locust tree, three cups of thin wine.
    Who could have foreseen returning alive from this journey?
    All the ten thousand affairs of the world, I entrust to Heaven.
  footnotes:
    - The 'waystation' (역관) refers to an official way-station where travelers rested during long journeys in classical Korea and China. The poem captures a moment of rest and reflection during travel.
